Since we can now get issues using a filter, it would be nice if we could create filters using SOAP.

this is a feature to consider, what do you think?

We plan to implement Jira in our company and for this we must prove that regular updates from our old issue tracking system are possible. For this I am writing a Jira service that should get all the issues that have changed in the old system and create/update the issues in Jira.

As a first step I try to simply create a trivial issue from a my own service that is running in Jira:

public void run() {
            ...

            ImportUtils.setSubvertSecurityScheme(true); // stolen form Mantis import code - necessary?
            ImportUtils.setIndexIssues(false);

            IssueManager issueManager = ManagerFactory.getIssueManager();
            GenericValue project = ManagerFactory.getProjectManager().getProjectByName("Test Project");            

            Map fields = new HashMap();
            fields.put("projectId", project.getLong("id"));
            fields.put(IssueFieldConstants.REPORTER, "admin");
            fields.put(IssueFieldConstants.ASSIGNEE, "admin");
            fields.put(IssueFieldConstants.ISSUE_TYPE, "" + IssueFieldConstants.NEWFEATURE_TYPE_ID);
            fields.put(IssueFieldConstants.SUMMARY, "automatic test bug");
            fields.put(IssueFieldConstants.STATUS, "" + IssueFieldConstants.OPEN_STATUS_ID);

            GenericValue issue = issueManager.createIssue("admin", fields);
 }

