In JIRA there is a global 'Use' permission, by default assigned to 'jira-users', which by default all users are a member.  If one accidentally removes oneself or others from the 'jira-users' group, most operations appear to work, but some prompt you for login (eg. accessing the user profile, or configuring issue navigator columns).  The lack of obvious cause and effect can be confusing.
